@@eThe Saltglass Reach -- Harbor Warden Jurisdictional Declaration@@N

This is not a distant region report. This is @@your threshold@@N.

The Saltglass Reach is where Mafdet's jurisdiction begins. Every
overland convoy that reaches our Ledger House counters crossed the
Reach's glass and salt on foot. The @@yShoreward Conversion@@N -- the
process by which inland law becomes maritime law -- is @@rour
process@@N, maintained by @@rour@@N Assessors, sworn at @@rour@@N Shrine.

The @@WMirror Flats@@N are our outer boundary. From the signal towers,
the Flats' salt crust reveals approaching caravans for miles.
@@gWe see them before they see us.@@N By design.

The @@rGlasswind Belts@@N are our natural defense and our deepest scar.
The thermal pulse that destroyed the Scorched Wastes fused our sand
into brittle glass. We built on that glass. Every guardian-name
sworn at the Shrine acknowledges this: @@dwe are the city the
disaster made@@N.

The @@yTariff Cairn Lines@@N fed directly into our Ledger Houses. Three
parallel routes -- Swift Line, Heavy Road, Sealed Route -- each
required different attestation. Our four Ledger Houses descend from
those cairn assessors. The @@rQuarantine Ledger@@N descends from the
Sealed Route's relic handlers, who classified pyramid-origin
artifacts before Mafdet had walls.

The @@WShoreward Seal@@N at the Tidemouth Dunes is where the Dual-
Attestation Protocol takes physical form. Inland provenance verified
against charter stamps. Maritime risk assessed against vessel and
season. Both must align before the harbor chain drops. @@yNo
exceptions. No appeals to urgency. No waivers for rank.@@N

The @@gReach Wardens@@N patrolling the cairn lines are our first
intelligence. When their reports indicate disrupted caravans or
unattested cargo in the Glasswind Belts, the Harbor Wardens raise
the chain and the Ledger Houses increase inspection thresholds.

The @@dGlasswalk Guides@@N are @@ystrictly neutral@@N. They guide anyone who
pays. That is honest commerce. But we note who they guide, when,
and from which direction.

The @@rRed Sand Outriders@@N from our debt-leverage consortium prey on
distressed caravans -- but bring goods otherwise lost. The Ledger
Houses process their cargo under amber-seal protocols. Mafdet pays
fairly, and fairly includes uncomfortable means of arrival.
Salt remembers the river. Glass remembers the
catastrophe. Cairns remember the old law. The @@yShoreward Conversion
remembers all of it@@N, translating broken history into clean manifests
and sworn oaths. @@dThat is what we are.@@N
